Franco Fogliato Honored for Excellence in Retail Sporting Goods

Mr. Fogliato is directing the European operations of Columbia Sportswear

PETIT-LANCY, SWITZERLAND, March 13, 2015, Franco Fogliato, Senior Vice President and General Manager of Europe Branding at Columbia Sportswear Company, has been named a Worldwide Branding Executive of the Year in Retail Sporting Goods for a third time. While inclusion in Worldwide Branding is an honor, only small selections of members in each discipline are chosen for this distinction. These special honorees are distinguished based on their professional accomplishments, academic achievements, leadership abilities, years of service, and the credentials they have provided in association with their Worldwide Branding membership.
With nearly two decades of retail experience, Mr. Fogliato has standout skills in brand management, marketing, and distribution, in which he has always been involved. His duties in his current role of two years are running the entire European territory and reporting to the international chief executive officer. He is also developing effective business strategies and serving on the executive board. He is managing profit and loss and the balance sheets of the Columbia Sportswear Group of brands.
Mr. Fogliato was the chief executive officer of Europe with GSM Europe, also a sporting goods retailer, from 2004 to 2013, before leaving to accept his current position. In the future, Mr. Fogliato plans for continued professional growth and success, which he attributes to his extensive background in business. He enjoys the environment in which he works, and combines it with a passion for business. He is committed to continuing to create shareholders’ value in long-term growth.
Mr. Fogliato became involved in his profession because he developed an interest in sports at an early age, and one of his many hobbies is jogging. Complementing Mr. Fogliato’s professional experience is his education. He earned an MBA in general management from the Open University in 2012.
In recognition of his achievements, Mr. Fogliato has been previously recognized numerous times by Worldwide Branding. He was named a VIP Member three times and an Elite American (http://eliteworldwideprofessionals.com/2014/05/01/franco-fogliato) twice. He was chosen to be profiled in the “Top 101 Industry Experts” book and featured in Pro-Files Magazine. He has appeared in the online newsletter (https://membernewsletters.files.wordpress.com/2014/08/franco-fogliato-1496670-newsletter.pdf) and been the subject of a career video. In addition to Worldwide Branding, he also maintains affiliations with various charitable organizations.
Columbia Sportswear Company is a renowned manufacturer that provides outdoor apparel and products. For more information about the company, visit http://www.columbia.com.


About Worldwide Who’s Who©
With over 500,000 members representing every major industry, Worldwide Who’s Who is a powerful networking resource that enables professionals to outshine their competition, in part through effective branding and marketing. Worldwide Who’s Who employs similar public relations techniques to those utilized by Fortune 500 companies, making them cost-effective for members who seek to take advantage of its career enhancement and business advancement services.
Worldwide Who’s Who membership provides individuals with a valuable third-party endorsement of their accomplishments, and gives them the tools needed to brand themselves and their businesses effectively. In addition to publishing biographies in print and electronic form, it offers an online networking platform where members can establish new professional relationships.
For more information, please visit http://www.worldwidewhoswho.com.



